item.title: Learning R Part 3
item.description: Learning R Part 3 Part 3, this chapter is all about R objects and I’m not excited. R objects, from what I’ve gathered are barely objects. We start this chapter with a bunch of different data types. R has six basic atomic vector data types: doubles, integers, characters, logicals, complex, and raw. > die <- c(1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6) > die [1] 1 2 3 4 5 6 > is.
